cockfight
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:[A complex of various esp. Sc dial. uses of <i>cock (cock's-headlin </i> .us;to ride cockie-breekie, cock-a-legs) for a boys' game in which one mounts on another's shoulders with the form <i>cock-fight</i>; cf <i>cocki</i>e n (Sc) in various combinations.]
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1932 (Turner Dannevirke) Cockfight: Game where boys take one another pick-a-back and try and push each other over. ca1940 Havelock children; c1941 St Patrick's College, Silverstream. 1953 14 M A17 Thames DHS 20 COCK-FIGHTS [unorganised games]
